parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unintended acceleration can cause loss of vehicle control, increasing the risk of accidents and injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle accelerates without input from the driver
the vehicle surges forward unexpectedly.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Electrical system failures can cause the vehicle to stall or shut down, leading to a loss of power and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The vehicle turns off completely and then restarts
the vehicle stalls without warning
the vehicle decelerates rapidly without input from the driver.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: EPB failure can cause the vehicle to become stuck, making it difficult or impossible to drive, and potentially leading to accidents or strandings.
symptoms: The EPB activates unexpectedly
the EPB fails to disengage
the vehicle becomes stuck.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Computer system failures can cause incorrect information to be displayed, leading to confusion and potentially affecting vehicle performance and safety.
symptoms: The fuel mile range is incorrectly reported
the electronic range and fuel range electronic detection system malfunctions.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission overheating and failure can cause the vehicle to stop driving suddenly, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The transmission overheats
the vehicle stops driving suddenly
the transmission slips or hesitates
the vehicle experiences sudden loss of power.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The transmission hesitation and stuttering can cause the vehicle to lose power and acceleration, leading to a loss of control and increasing the risk of accidents.
symptoms: The transmission hesitates when shifting into drive or reverse
the RPMs fluctuate erratically
the vehicle stutters when accelerating from a complete stop.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The brake failure can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brakes do not work
the vehicle rolls backwards or forwards without control
the brakes engage suddenly or erratically.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The unintended vehicle movement can cause the vehicle to lose control, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The vehicle moves in an unintended direction
the vehicle rolls backwards or forwards without control
the vehicle accelerates or decelerates without input from the driver.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of airbags to deploy in a crash can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as the vehicle's occupants are not adequately protected.
symptoms: Airbags do not deploy in a crash
despite the severity of the impact.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Improper airbag deployment can cause injuries or fatalities, as the airbag may not provide adequate protection or may even cause harm to the occupants.
symptoms: Airbag deploys incorrectly
such as only partially inflating or deploying unevenly
which can cause injuries to the occupants.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Seatbelt failure can lead to serious injuries or fatalities, as the occupants are not adequately restrained in the event of a crash.
symptoms: Seatbelt locks up or fails to lock
causing the occupant to be unrestrained or improperly restrained in a crash.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The malfunction of the brake auto hold system can cause the vehicle to stop suddenly, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brake auto hold system disengages and applies the parking brake unexpectedly
causing the vehicle to stop suddenly
and the parking brake cannot be disengaged until the seat belt is rebuckled.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Premature brake wear and noise can lead to reduced stopping power, potentially causing accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The brakes exhibit excessive wear
loud sounds
and screeching noises
requiring frequent replacements and repairs.

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Forward Collision Mitigation System False Activation
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The false activation of the forward collision mitigation system can cause the vehicle to brake suddenly, potentially leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The forward collision mitigation system activates unexpectedly
causing the vehicle to brake suddenly
even when there are no hazards or objects obstructing the vehicle.
